P. |last4=Fan |first4=Shaohua |last5=Philippe |first5=Herv\u00e9 |last6=MacCallum |first6=Iain |last7=Braasch |first7=Ingo |last8=Manousaki |first8=Tereza |last9=Schneider |first9=Igor |journal=Nature |volume=496 |issue=7445 |pages=311\u20136 |display-authors=9 |pmid=23598338 |pmc=3633110|bibcode = 2013Natur.496..311A |last10=Rohner |first10=Nicolas |last11=Organ |first11=Chris |last12=Chalopin |first12=Domitille |last13=Smith |first13=Jeramiah J. |last14=Robinson |first14=Mark |last15=Dorrington |first15=Rosemary A. |last16=Gerdol |first16=Marco |last17=Aken |first17=Bronwen |last18=Biscotti |first18=Maria Assunta |last19=Barucca |first19=Marco |last20=Baurain |first20=Denis |last21=Berlin |first21=Aaron M. |last22=Blatch |first22=Gregory L. |last23=Buonocore |first23=Francesco |last24=Burmester |first24=Thorsten |last25=Campbell |first25=Michael S. |last26=Canapa |first26=Adriana |last27=Cannon |first27=John P. |last28=Christoffels |first28=Alan |last29=De Moro |first29=Gianluca |last30=Edkins |first30=Adrienne L. }}\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-22184556 'Living fossil' coelacanth genome sequenced] BBC News Science & Environment; 17 April 2013\n\n{{Sarcopterygii}}\n{{Diversity of fish}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q59166}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Coelacanthiformes| ]]\n[[Category:Latimeriidae]]\n[[Category:Live-bearing fish]]\n[[Category:Ovoviviparous fish]]\n[[Category:Fish of the Comoros]]\n[[Category:Fish of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Fish of Kenya]]\n[[Category:Fish of Mozambique]]\n[[Category:Marine fish of South Africa]]\n[[Category:Fish of Tanzania]]\n[[Category:Extant Early Devonian first appearances]]\n[[Category:1938 in biology]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Lev Berg]]\n", "name_user": "RonKimble", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAppearances in popular culture", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coelacanth"}
{"title_page": "Lodderena ornata", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| taxon = Lodderena ornata\n| image = Lodderena ornata 01.jpg\n| image_caption = \n| authority =  (Olsson & McGinty, 1958)\n| synonyms_ref = \n| synonyms = \n* ''Cyclostremiscus emeryi'' <small>auct. non Ladd, 1966</small> \n* ''Cyclostremiscus ornatus'' <small>Olsson & McGinty, 1958</small> \n* ''Cyclostremiscus solitarius'' <small>Hertlein & Allison, 1968</small> \n* ''Pachystremiscus ornata'' <small>Olsson & McGinty, 1958</small> \n}}\n\n'''''Lodderena ornata''''' is a [[species]] of minute [[sea snail]], a marine [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Skeneidae]].<ref name=\"WoRMS\">{{WRMS species|224556|''Lodderena ornata'' (Olsson & McGinty, 1958)||21 April 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe size of the shell is 0.8&nbsp;mm.\n{{Expand section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==Distribution==\nThis marine species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off the [[Cape Verde Islands]], the [[Gulf of Guinea]], off [[Brazil]]; in the [[Gulf of Mexico]] and the [[Caribbean Sea]]. It has also been reported in the [[Indian Ocean]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* Olsson, A. A. and T. L. McGinty. 1958. ''Recent marine mollusks from the Caribbean coast of Panama with the description of some new genera and species.'' Bulletins of American Paleontology 39: 1\u201358, pls. 1\u20135.\n* Rol\u00e1n E., 2005. ''Malacological Fauna From The Cape Verde Archipelago. Part 1, Polyplacophora and Gastropoda''\n\n==External links==\n* {{Gastropods.com|key=9|id=16379|title=''Lodderena ornata''|access-date=16 January 2019}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q6666212}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lodderena Ornata}}\n[[Category:Lodderena|ornata]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of the Atlantic Ocean]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Gastropods of Cape Verde]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of Mexico]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 1958]]\n\n\n{{Trochoidea-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| taxon = Lodderena ornata\n| image = Lodderena ornata 01.jpg\n| image_caption = \n| authority =  (Olsson & McGinty, 1958)\n| synonyms_ref = \n| synonyms = \n* ''Cyclostremiscus emeryi'' <small>auct. non Ladd, 1966</small> \n* ''Cyclostremiscus ornatus'' <small>Olsson & McGinty, 1958</small> \n* ''Cyclostremiscus solitarius'' <small>Hertlein & Allison, 1968</small> \n* ''Pachystremiscus ornata'' <small>Olsson & McGinty, 1958</small> \n}}\n\n'''''Lodderena ornata''''' is a [[species]] of minute [[sea snail]], a marine [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Skeneidae]].<ref name=\"WoRMS\">{{WRMS species|224556|''Lodderena ornata'' (Olsson & McGinty, 1958)||21 April 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe size of the shell is 0.8&nbsp;mm.\n{{Expand section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==Distribution==\nThis marine species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off the [[Cape Verde Islands]], the [[Gulf of Guinea]], off [[Brazil]]; in the [[Gulf of Mexico]] and the [[Caribbean Sea]]. It has also been reported in the [[Indian Ocean]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* Olsson, A. A. and T. L. McGinty. 1958. ''Recent marine mollusks from the Caribbean coast of Panama with the description of some new genera and species.'' Bulletins of American Paleontology 39: 1-58, pls. 1\u20135.\n* Rol\u00e1n E., 2005. ''Malacological Fauna From The Cape Verde Archipelago. Part 1, Polyplacophora and Gastropoda''\n\n==External links==\n* {{Gastropods.com|key=9|id=16379|title=''Lodderena ornata''|access-date=16 January 2019}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q6666212}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lodderena Ornata}}\n[[Category:Lodderena|ornata]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of the Atlantic Ocean]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Gastropods of Cape Verde]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of Mexico]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 1958]]\n\n\n{{Trochoidea-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lodderena_ornata"}
{"title_page": "Naval Base Capt (N) P.N. Sacharia", "text_new": "{{Infobox military installation\n|name= Naval Base Capt (N) P.N. Sacharia\n|ensign= \n|native_name= \n|partof= <!-- for elements within a larger site -->\n|location= \n|nearest_town= [[Walvis Bay]]<!-- used in military test site infobox -->\n|country= {{NAM}}\n|image= \n|caption= \n|pushpin_map= \n|pushpin_label_position= \n|pushpin_mapsize= \n|pushpin_map_caption= \n|coordinates= \n|type= [[Naval base]]\n|site_area= <!-- area of site m2, km2 square mile etc -->\n|height= <!-- height of tallest part, not above sea level -->\n|ownership= [[Ministry of Defence (Namibia)]]<!--government department such as the MoD or the United States DoD-->\n|operator= [[Namibian Navy]] <!--where different from ownership such as the RAF or the USAF-->\n|controlledby= [[Namibian Defence Force]] <!--such as RAF Bomber Command or the Eighth Air Force-->\n|open_to_public= <!--for out of use sites/sites with museums etc-->\n|condition= Active\n|built= 2002<!-- {{Start date|YYYY}} -->\n|builder= \n|used= <!--{{End date|1946}} -->\n|materials= \n|fate= <!--changed from demolished parameter-->\n|battles= \n|events= \n|current_commander= Capt (N) Armas Igonda\n|past_commanders= [[Sinsy Nghipandua]]<!-- past notable commander(s) -->\n|garrison= <!-- such as the 25th Bombardment Group -->\n|occupants= <!-- squadrons only -->\n|TC= \n|LID= \n|GPS= \n|WMO= \n|website= \n|footnotes= \n}}\n'''Naval Base Capt (N) P.N. Sacharia''' is the [[Namibian Navy]]'s largest [[naval base]], situated at [[Walvis Bay]].<ref>https://neweralive.na/posts/namibian-navy-celebrates-15-years-of-existence</ref> The base provides Naval support functions to the Namibian Navy and hosts the Navy Command.\n\n==History==\nIn 1998 following the first graduation of the Namibian Navy Pioneer officers in Brazil, the site, north of the port of Walvis Bay identified as a potential Naval Base. After the ministry of Defence bought the piece of land, construction then started of the facility in 2002. In 2011 the construction of the 200 meter long jetty commenced and was completed afterwards.\n\nThe Base was commissioned in 2012 by president [[Hifikepunye Pohamba]].<ref>https://neweralive.na/posts/namibian-navy-celebrates-15-years-of-existence</ref> A bust of Capt (N) sacharia stands and the gate of the Base and is dedicated to Sailors that have passed on in the line of duty. At this occasion the [[NS Elephant]] and jetty were commissioned as well. Dredging of the seabed was done to seven meters<ref>https://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=99746&page=archive-read</ref>\n\n==Current Status==\nThe base is the [[homeport]] of the Navy fleet. It also currently hosts the Navy Command, the Navy Operations and navy Support and fleet headquarters. As headqaurters of the Navy all change of Navy command parades are held here.<ref>https://www.namibiansun.com/news/navy-sees-change-of-command</ref><ref>https://www.namibiansun.com/news/navy-sees-change-of-command</ref>\n\n==Commanding officers==\n2005-2009  Capt (N) Sinsy Nghipandua<ref>http://www.erongo.com.na/news/namibian-navy-sees-first-change-of-command</ref><br />\nunknown date- 31 October 2017 Capt(N) Richard Kopano<br />\n31 October 2017- Incumbent Capt(N) Armas Iigonda\n\n\n\n{{Post-start|caption=Naval Base Capt (N) P.N. Sacharia|float=}}\n{{Post-header|post-name=Commandant}}\n{{Post-member|from-date=2005|post-incumbent=Capt (N) [[Sinsy Nghipandua]]<ref>http://www.erongo.com.na/news/namibian-navy-sees-first-change-of-command</ref> ||to-date=2009}}\n{{Post-member|from-date=2009|post-incumbent=Capt (N) Richard Kopano ||to-date=31 October2017}}\n{{Post-member|from-date=31 October 2017|post-incumbent=Capt (N) Armas Iigonda ||to-date=Incubent}}\n<!--{{Post-member|from-date=XXX|post-incumbent=XXX|to-date=XXX}} -->\n{{Post-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Military of Namibia]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Namibia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military installation\n|name= Naval Base Capt (N) P.N. Sacharia\n|ensign= \n|native_name= \n|partof= <!-- for elements within a larger site -->\n|location= \n|nearest_town= [[Walvis Bay]]<!-- used in military test site infobox -->\n|country= {{NAM}}\n|image= \n|caption= \n|pushpin_map= \n|pushpin_label_position= \n|pushpin_mapsize= \n|pushpin_map_caption= \n|coordinates= \n|type= [[Naval base]]\n|site_area= <!-- area of site m2, km2 square mile etc -->\n|height= <!-- height of tallest part, not above sea level -->\n|ownership= [[Ministry of Defence (Namibia)]]<!--government department such as the MoD or the United States DoD-->\n|operator= [[Namibian Navy]] <!--where different from ownership such as the RAF or the USAF-->\n|controlledby= [[Namibian Defence Force]] <!--such as RAF Bomber Command or the Eighth Air Force-->\n|open_to_public= <!--for out of use sites/sites with museums etc-->\n|condition= Active\n|built= 2002<!-- {{Start date|YYYY}} -->\n|builder= \n|used= <!--{{End date|1946}} -->\n|materials= \n|fate= <!--changed from demolished parameter-->\n|battles= \n|events= \n|current_commander= Capt (N) Armas Igonda\n|past_commanders= [[Sinsy Nghipandua]]<!-- past notable commander(s) -->\n|garrison= <!-- such as the 25th Bombardment Group -->\n|occupants= <!-- squadrons only -->\n|TC= \n|LID= \n|GPS= \n|WMO= \n|website= \n|footnotes= \n}}\n'''Naval Base Capt (N) P.N. Sacharia''' is the [[Namibian Navy]]'s largest [[naval base]], situated at [[Walvis Bay]].<ref>https://neweralive.na/posts/namibian-navy-celebrates-15-years-of-existence</ref> The base provides Naval support functions to the Namibian Navy and hosts the Navy Command.\n\n==History==\nIn 1998 following the first graduation of the Namibian Navy Pioneer officers in Brazil, the site, north of the port of Walvis Bay identified as a potential Naval Base. After the ministry of Defence bought the piece of land, construction then started of the facility in 2002. In 2011 the construction of the 200 meter long jetty commenced and was completed afterwards.\n\nThe Base was commissioned in 2012 by president [[Hifikepunye Pohamba]].<ref>https://neweralive.na/posts/namibian-navy-celebrates-15-years-of-existence</ref> A bust of Capt (N) sacharia stands and the gate of the Base and is dedicated to Sailors that have passed on in the line of duty. At this occasion the [[NS Elephant]] and jetty were commissioned as well. Dredging of the seabed was done to seven meters<ref>https://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=99746&page=archive-read</ref>\n\n==Current Status==\nThe base is the [[homeport]] of the Navy fleet. It also currently hosts the Navy Command, the Navy Operations and navy Support and fleet headquarters. As headqaurters of the Navy all change of Navy command parades are held here.<ref>https://www.namibiansun.com/news/navy-sees-change-of-command</ref><ref>https://www.namibiansun.com/news/navy-sees-change-of-command</ref>\n\n==Commanding officers==\n2005-2009  Capt (N) Sinsy Nghipandua<ref>http://www.erongo.com.na/news/namibian-navy-sees-first-change-of-command</ref><br />\nunknown date- 31 October 2017 Capt(N) Richard Kopano<br />\n31 October 2017- Incumbent Capt(N) Armas Iigonda\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Military of Namibia]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Namibia]]\n", "name_user": "ViceAdmiral", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCommanding officers", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naval_Base_Capt_(N)_P.N._Sacharia"}
